23.24	Rasa_(aesthetics)	Rasa (aesthetics)	A rasa (Sanskrit: lit. 'juice' or 'essence') denotes an essential mental state and is the dominant emotional theme of a work of art or the primary feeling that is evoked in the person that views, reads or hears such a work.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f0/Mani_Madhava_Chakyar-Sringara-new.jpg/200px-Mani_Madhava_Chakyar-Sringara-new.jpg
